Defendant in custody.   
Defendant is before the Court for sentencing his probation having been revoked effective 10-06-16.   
Count 1 - Defendant is sentenced to the Wisconsin State Prison System for a total sentence of four (4) years.   Two (2) years initial confinement, followed by two (2) years extended supervision, concurrent with 15 CF 2 but consecutive to 14 CF 526.   Conditions of extended supervision are:
1) Maintain fulltime employment, schooling and work towards his high school diploma, GED or HSED;
2) Assessment/treatment/counseling as deemed appropriate by the Department's assessment process;
3) AODA assessment and follow through; 
4) Maintain absolute sobriety; 
5) Submit to random urine screens and pay for same; 
6) Pay costs of action; 
7) Pay supervision fees in an amount to be determined by DOC; 
8) No contact with any victim unless approved by the agent, except contact with Todd Ward as allowed;
9) Defendant is to have no contact with any of the co-defendants.  
Defendant is given credit for 38 days already served.   
Court finds the defendant is eligible for the Challenge Incarceration Program and for the Substance Abuce Program.   
Count 11 and Count 12 - Defendant is sentenced to nine (9) months jail on each count concurrent and concurrent with count 1, but consecutive to 14 CF 526.   
Minutes.

Defendant in custod
The State files an Amended Information which adds counts 11 and 12, criminal trespass to dwelling and misdemeanor theft, contrary to Sections 943.14 and 943.20(1)(a) of the Wisconsin Statutes.
NO CONTEST plea entered to count 1 of the amended Information, felony bail jumping.
NO CONTEST plea entered to count 11 of the amended Information, criminal trespass.
NO CONTEST plea entered to count 12 of the amended Information, misdemeanor theft.
The State moves to dismiss and read in counts 2, 3, 4, 5, 6, 7, 8, 9 and 10; six counts bail jumping, one count PTC burglary, one count drug paraphernalia and one count PTC criminal damage.  Motion granted.
Sentence Withheld.  Defendant is placed on probation to DOC for three (3) years.
Conditions of probation:
1) Maintain fulltime employment, schooling and work towards his high school diploma, GED or HSED;
2) Assessment, treatment, counseling as deemed appropriate by the Departments assessment process;
3) AODA assessment and follow through;
4) Maintain absolute sobriety;
5) Submit to random urine screens and pay for same;
6) Pay court costs;
7) pay supervision fees in an amount to be determined by DOC;
8) no contact with any victim unless approved by the agent, except contact with Todd Ward as allowed;
9) defendant is to have no contact with any of the co-defendants;
10) provide DNA sample (court does not order any DNA surcharges);
11) pay restitution of $16.00 to Walgreens;
12) pay restitution of $200.00 to Daniel Abts;
13) On count 1, spend forty-five (45) days in the county jail, under the Huber Law, to begin immediately upon completion of the condition time imposed on 15 CF 2.
